        <abstract>
            <p>Gradation in the eye.</p> 
<p>Hooker intends to reply [to W. H. Harvey’s article in <hi rend="italic">Gard. Chron.</hi> (1860): 145–6].</p>  
<p>Discusses <hi rend="italic">Aspicarpa</hi> with respect to correlation.</p> 
            <p>Comments on monstrous animals.</p>
            <p>Discusses objections of Bronn and Asa Gray to natural selection. Cites parallel between natural selection and Newton’s concept of gravitation.</p>
            <p>Mentions German experiments on spontaneous generation.</p>
        </abstract>
